.TH AXT-PEEK 1
.SH NAME
axt-peek \- snapshot directories, metadata, and git state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B axt-peek
[\fIPATHS...\fR]
[\fB--json\fR|\fB--agent\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B axt-peek
returns a compact directory snapshot with path, kind, size, language, git
status, mtime, and summary data.
.SH OUTPUT
Human output is used for TTY stdout. Agent JSONL is used when stdout is not a
TTY. JSON output uses schema
.B axt.peek.v1.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --kind all|file|dir
Filter by entry kind.
.TP
.B --no-git
Disable git status lookup.
.TP
.B --changed
Show only dirty or untracked paths.
.TP
.B --json
Emit the canonical JSON envelope.
.TP
.B --agent
Emit summary-first JSONL.
